{
  "texts": [
    "Later, this view is refined such that the speaker only lies if they intend the hearer to believe the utterance.",
    "The suggestion that the speaker must intend to deceive is a common stipulation in literature on lies.",
    "According to the \"traditional account\" of lying:",
    "To lie = df.",
    "to make a believed-false statement to another person with the intention that the other person believe that statement to be true (Mahon, 2015)."
  ]
}